portant respects, the story of Billy Garland is the story of Los Angeles. After arriving in Southern California in 1890, he and his allies drove much of the city's historic expansion in the first two decades of the twentieth century. Then, from 1920 to 1932, he directed the city's bid for the 1932 Olympic Games. Garland's quest to host the Olympics provides an unusually revealing window onto a particular time, place, and way of life. Reconstructing the narrative from Garland's visionary notion to its consequential aftermath, Barry Siegel shows how one man's grit and imagination made California history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCity planningzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aHosting of sporting eventszCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aOlympic host city selectiony1932. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh  a1890.  a1920 to 1932.  a1932 olympics.  a1932.  aallies.  abilly garland.  acalifornia history.  acalifornia.  aconsequential aftermath.  agreat depression.  agrit.  ahistoric expansion.  alos angeles.  aolympic games.  aolympics.  aprince of realtors.  aseedy frontier village.  asouthern california.  atransformation.  aunited states.  avisionary notion.  awilliam may garland.  aworld famous metropolis.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of 